## {#margin-slide data-menu-title="The margin"}

[The margin]{.slide-title}

<hr>

The **margin** is the smallest perpendicular distance from the separating line to *any* training observation. The margin is like a buffer between the two classes. 

<!-- A wider buffer means new observations have to be more ambiguous before they are at risk of being misclassified.  -->

::: {#cell-margin-comparison .cell execution_count=4}

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display}
![](9_1_support_vector_classifier-SLIDES_files/figure-revealjs/margin-comparison-output-1.png){#margin-comparison width=1028 height=543 fig-align='center'}
:::
:::


