## {#hyperplane-sign-slide data-menu-title="Sign determines class"}

[Classification in $p$ dimensions]{.slide-title}

<hr>

The **maximal margin classifier** finds coefficients $\beta_0, \beta_1, \ldots, \beta_p$ by solving the maximal margin optimization problem.

The classifier still depends only on the **support vectors**.

. . .

<br>

The resulting decision boundary is a **maximal margin hyperplane** that divides the space into two half-spaces. 


For a new point $(x_1, \ldots, x_p)$, the **sign** of $\beta_0 + \beta_1 x_1 + \cdots + \beta_p x_p$ determines which class it is assigned to:


- **= 0**: the point is on the hyperplane
- **< 0**: the point is on one side → assigned to one class
- **> 0**: the point is on the other side → assigned to the other class

